.TH hypot 3
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lhypot\*O, \*Lcabs\*O, \*Lfabs\*O \- Euclidean distance calculation and complex absolute value
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
\*OMath Library (\*Llibm.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <math.h>
.PP
\*Ldouble hypot  (double \*Vx\*L, double \*Vy\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  hypotf (float  \*Vx\*L, float  \*Vy\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble cabs   (double \*Vx\*L, double \*Vy\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  cabsf  (float  \*Vx\*L, float  \*Vy\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble fabs   (double \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  fabsf  (float  \*Vx\*L);
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "hypot function"
.iX "cabs function"
.iX "fabs function"
.iX "max_float"
\*Lhypot(\|)\*O and \*Lhypotf(\|)\*O
compute the length of the hypotenuse of a
right triangle; where \*Vx\*O and \*Vy\*O represent the perpendicular sides
of a right triangle.
hypot(\*Vx\*O,\*Vy\*O) and hypotf(\*Vx\*O,\*Vy\*O)
are equivalent to \*Lsqrt(\*Vx\*O**2 + \*Vy\*O**2).
.PP
\*Lcabs(\|)\*O and \*Lcabsf(\|)\*O return the complex absolute value of x
and are equivalent to \*Lhypot(\|)\*O and \*Lhypotf(\|)\*O.
.PP
\*Lfabs(\|)\*O and \*Lfabsf(\|)\*O  compute the absolute value of x.
.\"
